This paper deals with the problem of robust linear regression in high-dimensional settings, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper proposes an integrated method for robust regression that relaxes strong assumptions about the nature of the feature matrix, such as feature independence and sub-Gaussian noise with low variance. This suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Statistics (cs.ST) sub-categories of arXiv CS.
